text = "\"Biag ni Lam-Ang\" (The Life of Lam-Ang) is an epic poem from the Ilocano people of the northern Philippines. It is one of the few epics from the pre-colonial period that has survived to the present day.

THE EPIC:
The story tells of Lam-Ang, a man of extraordinary strength and abilities who was born speaking and chose his own name. The epic follows his adventures as he:
• Searches for his father Don Juan
• Avenges his father's death
• Courts and marries the beautiful Ines Kannoyan
• Battles various enemies and supernatural creatures
• Dies and is resurrected through the loyalty of his animal companions

CULTURAL SIGNIFICANCE:
• Reflects pre-colonial Ilocano society and values
• Showcases indigenous Filipino storytelling traditions
• Demonstrates the importance of family honor and bravery
• Contains elements of animism and indigenous spirituality
• Preserved through oral tradition before being written down

EDUCATIONAL VALUE:
This game aims to make this important piece of Philippine cultural heritage accessible and engaging for modern learners, combining storytelling with interactive gameplay and educational assessments.

GAME CREDITS:
Lam-Ang Chronicles - An Educational RPG
Based on the Ilocano epic poem \"Biag ni Lam-Ang\"
Created with Godot Engine"
